                  Used in \S3.5 to assert that the Claude Code CLI
                  exposes no \texttt{--no-cache}, \texttt{--cache-key},
                  \texttt{--fresh-session}, \texttt{--disable-cache}, or
                  \texttt{--bypass-cache} flag. The closest documented
                  cache-related flag is
                  \texttt{--exclude-dynamic-system-prompt-sections},
                  whose stated purpose is to \emph{improve} prompt-cache
                  reuse, not bypass it. \texttt{--no-session-persistence}
                  is documented as ``Disable session persistence so
                  sessions are not saved to disk and cannot be resumed.
                  Print mode only.'' --- i.e.\ controls local session
                  state, not the upstream API cache.},
  url          = {https://code.claude.com/docs/en/cli-reference}
}

